[{'questionId': 0, 'question': 'Email Address (for us to share updates and contact you directly)', 'type': 'email', 'hidden': True, 'encryptedAnswer': {'ciphertext': 'yhq2HRMFQ1y9pDpYztaXsgLLKKYOVdLbMxoHI6BkXXDjstcAZBFX5cYj4HZf/fYR', 'encryptedSymmetricKey': ''}}, {'questionId': 1, 'question': 'Telegram username', 'type': 'short-answer', 'hidden': True, 'encryptedAnswer': {'ciphertext': 'Wd2vybI2zBVbrHNj6A80y2Vm0ZvkStKAn/Mh5F4lgQk=', 'encryptedSymmetricKey': ''}}, {'questionId': 2, 'question': 'Have you read and confirmed your project abides by the Program General Eligibility Policy? https://gitcoin.notion.site/Gitcoin-Grants-Beta-Round-Eligibility-b7fca9fd3c26450b89ded11caaa6497f', 'type': 'multiple-choice', 'hidden': True, 'answer': 'Yes'}, {'questionId': 3, 'question': 'Previous project funding sources (VC, grants, token sales, etc)', 'type': 'short-answer', 'hidden': False, 'answer': 'Filecoin Next Step Microgrant'}, {'questionId': 4, 'question': 'Total prior funding for project in USD', 'type': 'number', 'hidden': False, 'answer': '5000'}, {'questionId': 5, 'question': 'Number of team members', 'type': 'number', 'hidden': False, 'answer': '3'}, {'questionId': 6, 'question': 'Profiles or socials of other main team members publicly associated with project', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False, 'answer': 'Imad Abdallah, CEO, is a mechanical engineer working as a postdoc at ETH Zurich. He is an entrepreneur in wind energy, AI and blockchain. [https://www.linkedin.com/in/imadabdallah](https://www.linkedin.com/in/imadabdallah) [https://github.com/IAbda](https://github.com/IAbda) 

Yuri Jean Fabris, CTO, is a self-taught software engineer and associate blockchain researcher at iCoLab ([https://icolab.org.br](https://icolab.org.br/)). [https://github.com/blocknomad](https://github.com/blocknomad) [https://www.linkedin.com/in/yuri-jean-fabris](https://www.linkedin.com/in/yuri-jean-fabris/)

Romario Gomes, fullstack developer, is graduated in pharmacy and actively engaged in data science projects with R and Python. [https://github.com/romaro-gomes](https://github.com/romaro-gomes) [https://www.linkedin.com/in/romario-gomes/](https://www.linkedin.com/in/romario-gomes/)'}, {'questionId': 7, 'question': 'How old is the project? (Months)', 'type': 'number', 'hidden': False, 'answer': '16'}, {'questionId': 8, 'question': 'Describe your project in a few paragraphs (ideally including a problem statement, solution, roadmap, and timeline for implementation)', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': True, 'answer': 'Fractal Flows is a Decentralized Science application for aggregation, curation and unleashing of underlying hard evidences, which we call ‚Äúknowledge bits‚Äù (see examples: [https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1S0-LywB1QLUKVmERF1N7cdzgLAhBo1ZP](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1S0-LywB1QLUKVmERF1N7cdzgLAhBo1ZP)), and emergence of consensus reports around scientific claims via human-AI interactions. Anyone can contribute aggregating knowledge bits or adding their opinions and arguments and anyone can apply to become an official validator and curate contributions via an open process. All contributors get rewarded for their productive efforts with fractions of an IP-NFT representing a claim, which in the future can yield profits from scientific consensus reports sales or by selling the IP-NFT fractions in an open decentralized market. Fractal Flows is a decentralized autonomous platform without gatekeepers where normal citizens, domain experts and AI play intricate and delicate roles to push the open scientific process forward.

The project aims to solve two major problems in science: (1) the reproducibility crisis, which is generated by an obsolete publishing format for papers based on PDFs that don‚Äôt bring with it the artifacts or hard evidences necessary for others scientists to verify what is claimed on publications, thus lowering scientific variance and quality, and (2) the ever growing number of scientific papers being published every year making it difficult for a scientist (but not limited to, as other professionals and citizens in general can use the application to inform their decisions as well) to keep up with the state-of-the-art of their area of expertise or to have an overview of the scientific consensus of specific claims from other domains of knowledge without reviewing the whole literature related to it.

### Roadmap

**Q2 2023**

- Integrate MultiVerS evidence-aggregation classifier ([https://github.com/dwadden/multivers](https://github.com/dwadden/multivers)) with main application to automatically extract evidences from a pool of millions of Open Access paper abstracts indexed on an ElasticSearch instance.

**Q3 2023**

- Develop ‚Äúofficial validator‚Äù features. These validators are experts in specific domains of knowledge and, via an open process, they gain permissions to curate evidences that are aggregated by contributors;
- Implement the Research Objects standard ([https://www.researchobject.org/](https://www.researchobject.org/)) via an integration with DeSci Nodes publishing platform ([https://www.desci.com/nodes](https://www.desci.com/nodes)) to adopt enhanced publications as evidence;
- With the curated evidence, generate summaries using an open-source and reproducible LLM, like GPT4All [https://github.com/nomic-ai/gpt4all](https://github.com/nomic-ai/gpt4all).

**Q4 2023**

- Onboard scientists and gather feedback;
- Design and implement new branding/UI/UX.

**Q1 2024**

- Launch MVP;
- Marketing campaigns.'}, {'questionId': 9, 'question': 'How does your project support the mission or goals of DeSci?', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': True, 'answer': 'Fractal Flows is an open-source project aligned with Open Science principles and works towards unleashing hidden precious scientific knowledge usually forgotten in researchers hard drives and minds, with the ultimate objective being to emerge a scientific consensus report out of that via human-AI interactions and accelerate the pace of scientific innovation in the world.

By having no gatekeepers, the platform enables people, from scientists to citizens in general, to participate in the process of value creation in scientific research in a decentralized and permissionless way, and slice & dice IP rights into many pieces with tokenization, monetizing the right to resell, right to create derivatives, right to collateralize, right to destroy, etc.'}, {'questionId': 10, 'question': 'Describe how funds from the grants program will be used for your project.', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False, 'answer': 'Funds from the grants program will be used towards finishing Fractal Flows‚Äô proof-of-concept. In this context, the resources will be used for the following objectives:

- Integrate MultiVerS evidence-aggregation classifier ([https://github.com/dwadden/multivers](https://github.com/dwadden/multivers)) with main application to automatically extract evidences from a pool of millions of Open Access paper abstracts indexed on an ElasticSearch instance;
- Develop ‚Äúofficial validator‚Äù features. These validators are experts in specific domains of knowledge and, via an open process, they gain permissions to curate evidences that are aggregated by contributors;
- Implement the Research Object standard ([https://www.researchobject.org/](https://www.researchobject.org/)) via an integration with DeSci Nodes publishing platform ([https://www.desci.com/nodes](https://www.desci.com/nodes)) to adopt enhanced publications as evidence;
- With the curated evidence, generate summaries using an open-source and reproducible LLM, like GPT4All ([https://github.com/nomic-ai/gpt4all](https://github.com/nomic-ai/gpt4all));
- Design and implement new branding/UI/UX.'}, {'questionId': 11, 'question': 'If you participated in past grant rounds (i.e. DeSci GR15) using a different project payout wallet address, please share it here.', 'type': 'address', 'hidden': True, 'encryptedAnswer': {'ciphertext': 'B2LAgbBEjGsSNJVpawM0bkFVwEU1p12gbh6OT3Qx/CU=', 'encryptedSymmetricKey': ''}}, {'questionId': 12, 'question': 'If this project participated in past grant rounds, please share any new updates or milestones since the last round.', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False}, {'questionId': 13, 'question': 'Is there any other information you would like to share about your project, previous work, other project affiliations, or potential conflicts of interest? (or anything not covered elsewhere in this application that you feel is relevant to share)', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False, 'answer': '1. Fractal Flows is the only DeSci platform to integrate [Consider.it](http://Consider.it)  for social voting as a critical feature to involve normal citizens in the scientific consensus process. This is the probably the first real effort by a DeSci project to simplify the integration of normal citizens‚Äô opinions in the Open Science process;
2. Research Objects ([https://www.researchobject.org/](https://www.researchobject.org/)) integration. Research Object is an open standard for identification, aggregation and exchange of research resources (data, code, logs, workflows‚Ä¶) required to make research reproducible. 
3. Social media integration. We want to make individuals, researchers, startups, corporations and governments making claims pertaining to science and engineering accountable for what they say. For this end, we have developed a Twitter integration that enables people to use #FFclaimit on Twitter to automatically host claims on Fractal Flows. The Fractal Flows bot will then tweet back with a link to the hosted claim page for everyone to see and engage.
4. On-chain scientific validation. Every step towards validating a scientific claim on Fractal Flows, from hosting a claim to adding and curating an evidence, is done through smart contract interactions on the Ethereum blockchain.'}, {'questionId': 14, 'question': 'Does 50% of your team reflect the diversity of the community your project serves with a particular emphasis on including women, Black, Indigenous, and People of Color (BIPoC), individuals with disabilities, and members of the LGBTQ+ community?', 'type': 'multiple-choice', 'hidden': True, 'encryptedAnswer': {'ciphertext': 'pt7uA26cWWkxRIxjS0XVapDHzo9oQfO83hFUPRhX/98=', 'encryptedSymmetricKey': ''}}]

